{{Bagua}} '''Zhen''' (震) is one of the {{ill|Bagua|ja|八卦|qq=draft}}. Its trigram form is {{resize|125%|'''☳'''}} with the first {{ill|Yao (lines)|ja|爻|qq=draft}} being Yang (⚊) and the second and third Yao being Yin (⚋). It is also one of the {{ill|Sixty-Four Hexagrams|ja|六十四卦|qq=draft}}, known as {{ill|Zhen as Thunder|ja|震|1=Zhen (Bagua)|lt=Zhen為雷|qq=draft}}, consisting of Zhen below and Zhen above.
== Trigram Symbolism == The original meaning represents the emergence of a single Yang at the bottom, moving forward without limits. From this, it symbolizes the time of initiation, thunderclaps (the sound of {{ill|thunder|ja|雷|qq=draft}}), {{ill|dragons|ja|龍|qq=draft}}, {{ill|feet|ja|足|qq=draft}}, the eldest son, and young men. As a {{ill|cardinal direction|ja|方位|qq=draft}}, it represents {{ill|east|ja|東|qq=draft}}<ref>「[https://www.ndl.go.jp/koyomi/chapter3/s2.html 干支2方位神]」National Diet Library, accessed December 16, 2021.</ref> (corresponding to {{ill|Mao (Earthly Branch)|ja|卯|1=Rabbit (zodiac)|2=ja|3=卯|4=fr|5=Lapin (astrologie chinoise)|6=nl|7=Konijn (astrologie)|lt=Rabbit (卯)|1=Rabbit (zodiac)|lt=Rabbit (卯)|qq=draft}} in the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|地支|qq=draft}}). In modern society, it is associated with telecommunications, high-speed communication, and at times, deceit. Physically, it corresponds to hearing, the {{ill|liver|ja|肝臓|qq=draft}}, and {{ill|metabolism|ja|代謝|qq=draft}}.
In the {{ill|Na Jia|ja|納甲|qq=draft}} system, Zhen is associated with {{ill|Geng (Heavenly Stem)|ja|庚|1=Kanoe (庚)|qq=draft}}, the Metal element in {{ill|Wuxing (Chinese philosophy)|lt=Wuxing|ja|五行思想|1=Wuxing (Chinese philosophy)|2=ja|3=五行思想|lt=Five Elements (Wuxing)|qq=draft}}, and the {{ill|west|ja|西|qq=draft}} among the {{ill|Five Directions|ja|五方|qq=draft}}.
== Earlier Heaven Arrangement == In the {{ill|Fuxi Earlier Heaven Bagua|ja|伏羲先天八卦|qq=draft}}, Zhen is the fourth in sequence and is positioned as one of the four corner trigrams, representing {{ill|northeast|ja|北東|qq=draft}}. In terms of Yin-Yang transformation, it represents the emergence of one Yang.
