[[sn:Zhen (Bagua)]] [[ja:震]] [[ja:巽]] [[ja:太極]] [[ja:乾]] [[ja:兌]] [[ja:艮]] [[ja:離]] [[ja:九星]] [[ja:魔方陣]] [[ja:後天定位盤]] [[ja:五行思想]] [[ja:木]] [[ja:火]] [[ja:土]] [[ja:金]] [[ja:水]] [[ja:十干]] [[ja:十二支]] [[ja:八卦]] [[ja:易経]] [[ja:禹]] [[ja:夏王朝]] [[ja:洛水]] [[ja:洛書]] [[ja:河図洛書]] [[ja:陰陽道]] [[ja:方位]] [[ja:運勢]] [[ja:吉凶]] [[ja:一白水星]] [[ja:北]] [[ja:坎]] [[ja:二黒土星]] [[ja:坤]] [[ja:三碧木星]] [[ja:東]] [[ja:四緑木星]] [[ja:五黄土星]] [[ja:六白金星]] [[ja:七赤金星]] [[ja:西]] [[ja:八白土星]] [[ja:九紫火星]] [[ja:南]] [[ja:太陽系]] [[ja:相性]] [[ja:吉方位]] [[ja:易]] [[ja:高島易断]] [[ja:風水]] [[ja:気学]] [[ja:陰陽五行説]] [[ja:暦注]] [[en:draft:Zhen (Bagua)]] [[en:Zhen]] [[sn:Zhen]] [[nl:Donder (trigram)]] [[fr:Zh%C3%A8n]] [[ar:Zhen (Bagua)]]

{{Bagua|qq=}} '''Zhen''' (震) is one of the {{ill|Bagua|ja|八卦|qq=draft|qq=}}. Its trigram form is {{resize|125%|'''☳'''|qq=}} with the first {{ill|Yao (lines)|ja|爻|qq=draft|qq=}} being Yang (⚊) and the second and third Yao being Yin (⚋). It is also one of the {{ill|Sixty-Four Hexagrams|ja|六十四卦|qq=draft|qq=}}, known as {{ill|Zhen as Thunder|ja|震|1=Zhen (Bagua)|lt=Zhen為雷|qq=draft|qq=}}, consisting of Zhen below and Zhen above.
== Trigram Symbolism == The original meaning represents the emergence of a single Yang at the bottom, moving forward without limits. From this, it symbolizes the time of initiation, thunderclaps (the sound of {{ill|thunder|ja|雷|qq=draft|qq=}}), {{ill|dragons|ja|龍|qq=draft|qq=}}, {{ill|feet|ja|足|qq=draft|qq=}}, the eldest son, and young men. As a {{ill|cardinal direction|ja|方位|qq=draft|qq=}}, it represents {{ill|east|ja|東|qq=draft|qq=}}<ref>「[https://www.ndl.go.jp/koyomi/chapter3/s2.html 干支2方位神]」National Diet Library, accessed December 16, 2021.</ref> (corresponding to {{ill|Mao (Earthly Branch)|ja|卯|1=Rabbit (zodiac)|2=ja|3=卯|4=fr|5=Lapin (astrologie chinoise)|6=nl|7=Konijn (astrologie)|lt=Rabbit (卯)|1=Rabbit (zodiac)|lt=Rabbit (卯)|qq=draft|qq=}} in the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|地支|qq=draft|qq=}}). In modern society, it is associated with telecommunications, high-speed communication, and at times, deceit. Physically, it corresponds to hearing, the {{ill|liver|ja|肝臓|qq=draft|qq=}}, and {{ill|metabolism|ja|代謝|qq=draft|qq=}}.
In the {{ill|Na Jia|ja|納甲|qq=draft|qq=}} system, Zhen is associated with {{ill|Geng (Heavenly Stem)|ja|庚|1=Kanoe (庚)|qq=draft|qq=}}, the Metal element in {{ill|Wuxing (Chinese philosophy)|lt=Wuxing|ja|五行思想|1=Wuxing (Chinese philosophy)|2=ja|3=五行思想|lt=Five Elements (Wuxing)|qq=draft|qq=}}, and the {{ill|west|ja|西|qq=draft|qq=}} among the {{ill|Five Directions|ja|五方|qq=draft|qq=}}.
== Earlier Heaven Arrangement == In the {{ill|Fuxi Earlier Heaven Bagua|ja|伏羲先天八卦|qq=draft|qq=}}, Zhen is the fourth in sequence and is positioned as one of the four corner trigrams, representing {{ill|northeast|ja|北東|qq=draft|qq=}}. In terms of Yin-Yang transformation, it represents the emergence of one Yang.
