{{Bagua|qq=}}
'''Zhen''' (震) is one of the [[:en:Bagua|Bagua]]. Its trigram form is {{resize|125%|'''☳'''|qq=}} with the first {{ill|Yao (lines)|ja|爻|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yao (lines)|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yao (lines)|qq=}} being Yang (⚊) and the second and third Yao being Yin (⚋). It is also one of the [[:en:Hexagram (I Ching)|Sixty-Four Hexagrams]], known as {{ill|Zhen as Thunder|ja|震|1=Zhen (Bagua)|2=ja|3=震|lt=Zhen (震)|1=Zhen (Bagua)|lt=Zhen為雷|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Zhen as Thunder|13=User:Immanuelle/Zhen (Bagua)|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Zhen as Thunder|13=User:Immanuelle/Zhen (Bagua)|qq=}}, consisting of Zhen below and Zhen above.

== Trigram Symbolism ==
The original meaning represents the emergence of a single Yang at the bottom, moving forward without limits. From this, it symbolizes the time of initiation, thunderclaps (the sound of [[:en:Lightning|thunder]]), {{ill|dragons|ja|龍|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/dragons|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/dragons|qq=}}, [[:en:Foot|feet]], the eldest son, and young men. As a [[:en:Cardinal direction|Five directions]], it represents [[:en:East|east]]<ref>「[https://www.ndl.go.jp/koyomi/chapter3/s2.html 干支2方位神]」National Diet Library, accessed December 16, 2021.</ref> (corresponding to {{ill|Mao (Earthly Branch)|ja|卯|1=Rabbit (Zodiac)|lt=Rabbit (卯)|2=ja|3=卯|1=Rabbit (zodiac)|2=ja|3=卯|4=fr|5=Lapin (astrologie chinoise)|6=nl|7=Konijn (astrologie)|lt=Rabbit (卯)|1=Rabbit (zodiac)|lt=Rabbit (卯)|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mao (Earthly Branch)|13=User:Immanuelle/Rabbit (zodiac)|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mao (Earthly Branch)|13=User:Immanuelle/Rabbit (Zodiac)|qq=}} in the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|地支|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Earthly Branches|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Earthly Branches|qq=}}). In modern society, it is associated with telecommunications, high-speed communication, and at times, deceit. Physically, it corresponds to hearing, the [[:en:Liver|liver]], and [[:en:Metabolism|metabolism]].

In the {{ill|Na Jia|ja|納甲|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Na Jia|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Na Jia|qq=}} system, Zhen is associated with {{ill|Geng (Heavenly Stem)|ja|庚|1=Kanoe (庚)|lt=Kanoe (庚)|2=ja|3=庚|4=zh|5=庚|1=Kanoe (庚)|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Geng (Heavenly Stem)|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanoe (庚)|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Geng (Heavenly Stem)|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanoe (庚)|qq=}}, the Metal element in [[:en:Wuxing (Chinese philosophy)|Five Elements (Wuxing)]], and the [[:en:West|west]] among the {{ill|Five Directions|ja|五方|lt=Five Directions|1=Cardinal direction|2=ja|3=方位|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Five Directions|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Five Directions|13=User:Immanuelle/Cardinal direction|qq=}}.

== Earlier Heaven Arrangement ==
In the {{ill|Fuxi Earlier Heaven Bagua|ja|伏羲先天八卦|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fuxi Earlier Heaven Bagua|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fuxi Earlier Heaven Bagua|qq=}}, Zhen is the fourth in sequence and is positioned as one of the four corner trigrams, representing {{ill|northeast|ja|北東|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/northeast|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/northeast|qq=}}. In terms of Yin-Yang transformation, it represents the emergence of one Yang.

